  "text": "This domain is specifically oriented on the analysis of the role of \"web 2.0\"-and \"social media\"-platforms (Twitter, YouTube, Facebook, Wikipedia, blogs, etc) in documenting, analyzing and interpreting the crisis and finance in general. [CITATION_1] argues that web 2.0 contains a financial blogosphere that has analyzed the financial market in order to spur investments.",
